00:14:34.960 --> 00:14:36.100
- I don't think so.

266
00:14:36.170 --> 00:14:38.410
- They ran the tag of that car.

267
00:14:38.480 --> 00:14:41.370
and they saw it belonged to a Kristine Melton.

268
00:14:41.440 --> 00:14:44.960
- Kristine Melton was a 35-year-old young lady.

269
00:14:45.030 --> 00:14:47.340
who was-- she was a waitress.

270
00:14:47.410 --> 00:14:50.270
She had just come down from the state of Illinois

271
00:14:50.340 --> 00:14:51.790
with her family.

272
00:14:51.860 --> 00:14:56.370
- She had a cat named Monty that she was very fond of.

273
00:14:56.440 --> 00:14:58.890
And they just--everybody had nothing but nice things.

274
00:14:58.960 --> 00:15:00.750
really. to say about Kristine.

275
00:15:02.960 --> 00:15:06.310
- I have a feeling that she's in this car.

276
00:15:06.370 --> 00:15:11.270
- They went ahead and broke the driver's side window.

277
00:15:11.340 --> 00:15:12.580
- Oh. there is blood

278
00:15:12.650 --> 00:15:15.100
all on the inside of the passenger seat.

279
00:15:15.170 --> 00:15:17.200
Pop that trunk. Nothing?

280
00:15:24.270 --> 00:15:25.820
Nope.

281
00:15:27.820 --> 00:15:31.130
- We needed to find Kristine Melton right away.

282
00:15:31.200 --> 00:15:32.370
I am Trish Bell.

283
00:15:32.440 --> 00:15:35.620
I was the lead detective in the Wade Wilson case.

284
00:15:35.680 --> 00:15:37.410
We called her emergency contact.

285
00:15:37.480 --> 00:15:38.680
who put us in contact

286
00:15:38.750 --> 00:15:41.170
with her best friend. Stephanie Johnson.

287
00:15:41.240 --> 00:15:44.820
They had gone out that night to the Buddha bar.

288
00:15:48.370 --> 00:15:52.060
They met a gentleman-- or a man.

289
00:15:52.130 --> 00:15:54.790
Identified himself as JR.

290
00:15:54.860 --> 00:15:57.030
She identified him as Wade Wilson

291
00:15:57.100 --> 00:15:58.650
from a photo lineup.

292
00:15:58.720 --> 00:16:00.860
They had left the bar with JR

293
00:16:00.930 --> 00:16:03.930
and that had eventually gone back to her house.

294
00:16:04.000 --> 00:16:05.550
It was around 5:00 in the morning.

295
00:16:05.620 --> 00:16:08.100
Stephanie left in her car.

296
00:16:08.170 --> 00:16:11.270
and so it left Kristine Melton and Wade Wilson alone.

297
00:16:11.340 --> 00:16:12.890
alive and well.

298
00:16:15.820 --> 00:16:18.370
We had officers that were at her house break the door

299
00:16:18.440 --> 00:16:19.890
and go inside.

300
00:16:19.960 --> 00:16:21.650
and that's when we located her.

301
00:16:23.170 --> 00:16:26.620
She was discovered wrapped in some blankets and bedding.

302
00:16:26.680 --> 00:16:28.170
You really couldn't see her.

303
00:16:28.240 --> 00:16:30.550
but you could tell there was. like. a body in a hallway

304
00:16:30.620 --> 00:16:32.410
exiting her bedroom.

305
00:16:32.480 --> 00:16:35.650
He choked her out and killed her by asphyxiation.

306
00:16:35.720 --> 00:16:37.370
And then possibly after her death.

307
00:16:37.440 --> 00:16:39.060
he sexually assaulted her with objects

308
00:16:39.130 --> 00:16:42.410
that he found within the home.

309
00:16:42.480 --> 00:16:44.680
Wade Wilson was in a rage for that day.

310
00:16:44.750 --> 00:16:46.930
and we didn't think he was going to stop.

311
00:16:48.440 --> 00:16:51.370
- Right after it happened. I was interrogated.

312
00:16:51.440 --> 00:16:52.790
I didn't even know

313
00:16:52.860 --> 00:16:54.580
that he went home with a girl at that time.

314
00:16:54.650 --> 00:16:56.750
I just thought he stole my car

315
00:16:56.820 --> 00:16:59.650
with the guy he was gonna go do drugs with.

316
00:17:19.510 --> 00:17:21.720
I was so tired. I was still hurt.

317
00:17:21.790 --> 00:17:23.410
My nose was still bleeding.

318
00:17:23.480 --> 00:17:27.000
Every time I would cry. my nose started bleeding again.

319
00:17:42.790 --> 00:17:44.000
- Mm-hmm.

320
00:17:57.750 --> 00:18:00.650
He's been in and out of jail his whole life.

321
00:18:02.620 --> 00:18:04.650
He had a rape in Tallahassee

322
00:18:04.720 --> 00:18:06.930
that a jury found him not guilty.

323
00:18:07.000 --> 00:18:10.790
a beating and everything. brutal kidnapping. all that.

324
00:18:10.860 --> 00:18:13.550
I almost thought I could fix him.

325
00:18:13.620 --> 00:18:16.200
One time. he grabbed me by the hair

326
00:18:16.270 --> 00:18:20.060
and started banging my head against the headboard.

327
00:18:20.130 --> 00:18:23.340
He drug me into the shower. turned the shower on.

328
00:18:23.410 --> 00:18:25.860
and continued to beat me under the shower.

329
00:18:25.930 --> 00:18:28.890
And then he just sat on the toilet

330
00:18:28.960 --> 00:18:30.930
and kind of just watched me.

331
00:18:31.000 --> 00:18:34.480
almost like a demon took over him. and then left.

332
00:19:13.480 --> 00:19:15.480
- What does he say?

333
00:19:54.370 --> 00:19:55.620
I kept asking.

334
00:19:55.680 --> 00:19:57.510
so we don't know if this girl is okay or not yet?

335
00:20:23.550 --> 00:20:27.410
- The whole thing just kind of really hit me that--

336
00:20:27.480 --> 00:20:30.410
just surreal...

337
00:20:30.480 --> 00:20:34.410
to be able to absorb that somebody you were in love with

338
00:20:34.480 --> 00:20:37.060
was capable of doing anything like that.

339
00:21:32.440 --> 00:21:33.790
- 911. what is your emergency?

340
00:21:33.860 --> 00:21:36.000
- I would like to file a missing persons report.

341
00:21:36.060 --> 00:21:38.060
- Right around the same time.

342
00:21:38.130 --> 00:21:40.340
there was a missing person report.

343
00:21:40.410 --> 00:21:44.240
- She was walking to work. okay?

344
00:21:44.310 --> 00:21:46.680
And never made it to work.

345
00:21:46.750 --> 00:21:48.170
Her purse was found.

346
00:21:48.240 --> 00:21:50.410
and she is nowhere to be found.

347
00:21:50.480 --> 00:21:52.960
- Okay. And who is that to you?

348
00:21:53.030 --> 00:21:55.100
- That is my fiancée.

349
00:21:55.170 --> 00:21:57.650
- Which ended up to be Diane Ruiz.

350
00:21:57.720 --> 00:22:00.000
Is it possible for these two to be connected?

351
00:22:00.060 --> 00:22:04.060
Did Wade Wilson do something to this woman. too?

352
00:22:04.130 --> 00:22:07.200
She hadn't returned home. and that was out of the ordinary.

353
00:22:07.270 --> 00:22:11.060
- Her phone is not in her purse that they found.

354
00:22:11.130 --> 00:22:13.200
And I have called it numerous times.

355
00:22:13.270 --> 00:22:14.750
and it goes straight to voicemail.

356
00:22:14.820 --> 00:22:17.240
- Okay. we're going to get an officer to you. okay?

357
00:22:17.310 --> 00:22:19.930
- Thank you very much.

358
00:22:20.000 --> 00:22:21.440
- My name is Nicholas Jones.

359
00:22:21.510 --> 00:22:23.860
I'm a detective with the Cape Coral Police Department.

360
00:22:23.930 --> 00:22:25.410
and I was assigned

361
00:22:25.480 --> 00:22:29.550
to the Diane Ruiz missing person case.

362
00:22:29.620 --> 00:22:34.060
So I kind of left Detective Bell

363
00:22:34.130 --> 00:22:36.960
with the rest of our violent crimes unit

364
00:22:37.030 --> 00:22:40.820
and started this missing person investigation.

365
00:22:42.650 --> 00:22:46.000
- Diane--I think "loyal" would be a good description of her.

366
00:22:46.060 --> 00:22:50.060
She was very close to her fiancé.

367
00:22:50.130 --> 00:22:51.890
was a wonderful mom.

368
00:22:51.960 --> 00:22:53.750
She had a son and a daughter.

369
00:22:53.820 --> 00:22:56.820
And she worked at the Moose Lodge

370
00:22:56.890 --> 00:22:58.890
and was a bartender there.

371
00:22:58.960 --> 00:23:00.580
had lots of friends.

372
00:23:00.650 --> 00:23:01.890
She was very close to work.

373
00:23:01.960 --> 00:23:04.550
She lived very close from her house to work.

374
00:23:04.620 --> 00:23:05.960
It was a short walk.

375
00:23:06.030 --> 00:23:08.550
And where her purse was found

376
00:23:08.620 --> 00:23:10.890
was on that path.

377
00:23:10.960 --> 00:23:14.000
- We were waiting for some search dogs

378
00:23:14.060 --> 00:23:17.440
and aviation unit with the sheriff's office

379
00:23:17.510 --> 00:23:20.060
to come help search a wooded area

380
00:23:20.130 --> 00:23:22.170
where her purse was located.

381
00:23:22.240 --> 00:23:24.370
- There was never a night where

382
00:23:24.440 --> 00:23:27.510
we didn't kiss each other good night.

383
00:23:27.580 --> 00:23:29.890
And I'm missing that right now.

384
00:23:29.960 --> 00:23:32.860
- Diane Ruiz's family are still reeling

385
00:23:32.930 --> 00:23:35.890
from the sudden disappearance of the 43-year-old woman.

386
00:23:35.960 --> 00:23:37.580
And her son. Brandon Cuellar

387
00:23:37.650 --> 00:23:39.310
wants the nightmare to be over.

388
00:23:39.370 --> 00:23:41.060
- I want my mother to come home.

389
00:23:41.130 --> 00:23:43.310
That's my mother.

390
00:23:43.370 --> 00:23:45.930
- I was sitting in the car. and I got an email

391
00:23:46.000 --> 00:23:47.790
from the phone company

392
00:23:47.860 --> 00:23:50.650
with Diane Ruiz's phone records.

393
00:23:50.720 --> 00:23:53.720
I noticed that there were two phone calls that were made

394
00:23:53.790 --> 00:23:56.580
right after she had gone missing.

395
00:23:56.650 --> 00:23:58.240
I recognized the phone number

396
00:23:58.310 --> 00:24:02.930
of Wade Wilson's girlfriend. Mila.

397
00:24:03.000 --> 00:24:06.200
- We knew that Wade had Diane's phone.

398
00:24:06.270 --> 00:24:08.720
So that just made us believe even stronger

399
00:24:08.790 --> 00:24:10.550
that he had killed her as well.

400
00:24:10.620 --> 00:24:12.240
- My heart kind of just sank

401
00:24:12.310 --> 00:24:16.890
that we now have a second death investigation...

402
00:24:16.960 --> 00:24:20.200
Kristine Melton. Diane Ruiz.

403
00:24:20.270 --> 00:24:23.550
- I think he was just frantic. on a murdering high.

404
00:24:25.370 --> 00:24:27.060
So. in the sequence of events.

405
00:24:27.130 --> 00:24:29.680
he leaves Melton's house at 7:10.

406
00:24:33.510 --> 00:24:36.860
He batters Mila at almost 9:00 a.m....

407
00:24:39.860 --> 00:24:44.240
And then Diane Ruiz at 9:45.

408
00:24:44.310 --> 00:24:46.240
He's just a psychopath killer

409
00:24:46.310 --> 00:24:48.240
that likes to harm women.

410
00:24:50.890 --> 00:24:54.820
We needed to find Wade Wilson right away.

411
00:24:54.890 --> 00:24:56.310
- All bets are off.

412
00:24:56.370 --> 00:25:00.750
Everybody's involved. multiple agencies trying to locate him.

413
00:25:00.820 --> 00:25:02.340
- All right.

414
00:25:02.410 --> 00:25:06.860
- We made contact with his bio father. Steve Testasecca.

415
00:25:06.930 --> 00:25:09.270
- And she said. do you know where he's at?

416
00:25:09.340 --> 00:25:11.410
And I said. no. I don't know where he's at.

417
00:25:11.480 --> 00:25:14.060
And she said. have you heard from him?

418
00:25:14.130 --> 00:25:15.240
I said. yeah.

419
00:25:15.310 --> 00:25:17.060
- He said that he received a call from Wade.

420
00:25:17.130 --> 00:25:19.860
and he was acting almost boastful and proud.

421
00:25:19.930 --> 00:25:23.200
- And I'm hearing this man that I created--

422
00:25:23.270 --> 00:25:26.480
helped create...

423
00:25:26.550 --> 00:25:29.440
telling me the details

424
00:25:29.510 --> 00:25:31.650
of all these things...

425
00:25:31.720 --> 00:25:34.240
with joy in his voice. you know?

426
00:25:34.310 --> 00:25:37.480
It made me want to throw up.

427
00:25:37.550 --> 00:25:40.240
- Said that he killed two women

428
00:25:40.310 --> 00:25:42.890
and that he was hiding in a house

429
00:25:42.960 --> 00:25:45.750
close to where he had ran from us originally.

430
00:25:45.820 --> 00:25:48.310
- He's like. Dad. I need you to come get me.

431
00:25:48.370 --> 00:25:49.650
I'm in trouble.

432
00:25:49.720 --> 00:25:52.240
I said. listen. you got to tell me what's going on.

433
00:25:52.310 --> 00:25:55.310
And he started from the top.

434
00:25:57.340 --> 00:26:00.550
Just the details that he went into about Kristine--

435
00:26:00.620 --> 00:26:04.580
they had sex. and she fell asleep on the bed.

436
00:26:04.650 --> 00:26:07.960
Got on top of her and choked her to death.

437
00:26:08.030 --> 00:26:10.890
I hadn't even heard about...

438
00:26:10.960 --> 00:26:13.170
Diane's situation yet.

439
00:26:13.240 --> 00:26:16.200
But just the details that he went into about Kristine.

440
00:26:16.270 --> 00:26:18.750
you know. rolling her up in the bedding

441
00:26:18.820 --> 00:26:21.750
and tying her up and dragging her down.

442
00:26:21.820 --> 00:26:24.960
trying to get her to the car. but he couldn't.

443
00:26:25.030 --> 00:26:28.240
She was too heavy. you know?

444
00:26:28.310 --> 00:26:33.060
Hearing him describe those things to me...

445
00:26:33.130 --> 00:26:37.060
I can't explain that feeling. you know...

446
00:26:37.130 --> 00:26:39.890
from your kid. you know. your son.

447
00:26:45.890 --> 00:26:48.960
I knew Wade's mom. She got pregnant.

448
00:26:49.030 --> 00:26:51.240
I was 15. She was 14.

449
00:26:51.310 --> 00:26:53.890
And then I got in some trouble.

450
00:26:53.960 --> 00:26:55.650
And I ended up

451
00:26:55.720 --> 00:26:58.310
doing eight months in a juvenile program.

452
00:26:58.370 --> 00:27:02.060
And I got a legal document

453
00:27:02.130 --> 00:27:05.410
saying that she was...

454
00:27:05.480 --> 00:27:07.270
putting him up for adoption.

455
00:27:07.340 --> 00:27:09.270
I couldn't do anything about it.

456
00:27:09.340 --> 00:27:10.890
All I could think about--

457
00:27:10.960 --> 00:27:14.030
just that innocent kid. you know?

458
00:27:14.100 --> 00:27:16.440
And I just was-- in my mind. was like.

459
00:27:16.510 --> 00:27:18.200
how did we get here?

460
00:27:18.270 --> 00:27:20.680
You know what I mean? How did we get here?

461
00:27:20.750 --> 00:27:23.510
Because he wasn't raised like that.

462
00:27:23.580 --> 00:27:26.410
His adoptive family-- they're solid people.

463
00:27:26.480 --> 00:27:30.650
good people. hardworking. honest Christian people.

464
00:27:31.960 --> 00:27:33.930
- This is his son. and he loves him.

465
00:27:34.000 --> 00:27:37.410
but he's already admitting that he's killed two women.

466
00:27:37.480 --> 00:27:39.240
and he's afraid of what more would happen

467
00:27:39.310 --> 00:27:40.410
if he didn't call us.

468
00:27:40.480 --> 00:27:43.820
- I knew he enjoyed it.

469
00:27:43.890 --> 00:27:45.930
I knew...

470
00:27:46.000 --> 00:27:48.060
he wanted me to feel--

471
00:27:48.130 --> 00:27:49.820
I don't even think intentionally.

472
00:27:49.890 --> 00:27:53.200
he wanted me to feel his excitement.

473
00:27:53.270 --> 00:27:57.550
I just feel like he just was so amped up talking about it.

474
00:27:57.620 --> 00:27:59.240
I don't want to say joy.

475
00:27:59.310 --> 00:28:01.410
just adrenaline. maybe. you know?

476
00:28:01.480 --> 00:28:03.060
He wanted me to feel that.

477
00:28:03.130 --> 00:28:07.100
- He cooperated and ultimately got Wade Wilson.

478
00:28:07.170 --> 00:28:08.890
Said he would send him an Uber.

479
00:28:08.960 --> 00:28:10.720
and that's how he got the address

480
00:28:10.790 --> 00:28:13.480
to where Wade Wilson was located.

481
00:28:13.550 --> 00:28:16.060
- All right. buddy. I'm going to go do it down here.

482
00:28:16.130 --> 00:28:18.000
- Okay. That's cool. - Come on here. buddy.

483
00:28:18.060 --> 00:28:19.890
- Wade Wilson came out of the house

484
00:28:19.960 --> 00:28:21.720
and surrendered to law enforcement

485
00:28:21.790 --> 00:28:23.720
without any incident.

486
00:28:23.790 --> 00:28:26.100
- It's a hard decision. I promise you.

487
00:28:26.170 --> 00:28:29.130
And it's the worst decision I've ever had to make.

488
00:28:29.200 --> 00:28:30.890
- Face the fucking car. man. Spread your feet.

489
00:28:30.960 --> 00:28:32.720
- You know. fuck you. man. both: Fuck you.

490
00:28:32.790 --> 00:28:34.240
- Yeah. Yeah.

491
00:28:34.310 --> 00:28:36.060
- I don't care what anybody says.

492
00:28:36.130 --> 00:28:38.510
It doesn't bother me. because I know in my heart

493
00:28:38.580 --> 00:28:40.410
that I did the right thing.

494
00:28:40.480 --> 00:28:42.030
You know. I made the right choice.

495
00:28:42.100 --> 00:28:44.580
- I'm gonna put some new handcuffs on you.

496
00:28:44.650 --> 00:28:45.890
So. if you do anything stupid.

497
00:28:45.960 --> 00:28:47.410
I'm gonna slam you on your face.

498
00:28:47.480 --> 00:28:48.820
- Do I look stupid?

499
00:28:48.890 --> 00:28:50.750
You can slam me on my face if you want to--I don't care.

500
00:28:50.820 --> 00:28:52.060
I'm not gonna do nothing. - All right.

501
00:28:52.130 --> 00:28:53.580
- But you don't have to threaten me.

502
00:28:53.650 --> 00:28:56.580
I didn't do shit to you. - Wade. man. come on. stop.

503
00:28:56.650 --> 00:28:58.750
- Watch your neck. man. Nope.

504
00:28:58.820 --> 00:29:01.790
Put it in this way. Yep. I just don't want--

505
00:29:01.860 --> 00:29:03.340
- Now the question then became.

506
00:29:03.410 --> 00:29:05.820
was how we were going to put this together

507
00:29:05.890 --> 00:29:09.650
and what we needed in order to have a successful prosecution.

508
00:29:09.720 --> 00:29:12.620
- You can move those to the front.

509
00:29:12.680 --> 00:29:15.100
- It was probably 12:30. 1:00.

510
00:29:15.170 --> 00:29:17.410
He starts by asking me to take off his handcuffs.

511
00:29:17.480 --> 00:29:19.620
He says he'll tell me whatever I want to know.

512
00:29:19.680 --> 00:29:21.060
- All right. I'll make it work. Thank you.

513
00:29:21.130 --> 00:29:22.550
- Promise? - Can I just take them off?

514
00:29:22.620 --> 00:29:23.890
I'll be cool. - No.

515
00:29:23.960 --> 00:29:25.410
And I decline that offer.

516
00:29:25.480 --> 00:29:27.410
I think he would have tried to escape.

517
00:29:38.310 --> 00:29:42.030
I do believe that he probably would have attempted

518
00:29:42.100 --> 00:29:43.890
to do something if he got his cuffs off.

519
00:29:43.960 --> 00:29:46.060
He just murdered two women.

520
00:29:46.130 --> 00:29:48.410
I'm another woman in the room with him.

521
00:30:32.130 --> 00:30:33.720
Are you questioning me for something?

522
00:30:33.790 --> 00:30:34.890
- Throughout the interview.

523
00:30:34.960 --> 00:30:36.750
he tries to control the interview.

524
00:30:36.820 --> 00:30:39.060
He always thinks he's the smartest person in the room.

525
00:30:39.130 --> 00:30:42.370
He thinks that he's gonna get one up on you.

526
00:30:42.440 --> 00:30:45.580
He thinks he's charming and that he can charm any female.

527
00:31:08.270 --> 00:31:09.480
- Mm-hmm.

528
00:31:11.960 --> 00:31:13.000
- Hey.

529
00:31:22.270 --> 00:31:24.580
- He does have a presence about him.

530
00:31:24.650 --> 00:31:27.310
It's almost like when you're watching a scary movie

531
00:31:27.370 --> 00:31:29.240
and you're just waiting for something to happen.

532
00:31:29.310 --> 00:31:31.620
And that's kind of how I felt through the whole interview.

533
00:32:23.650 --> 00:32:25.750
- He was a difficult interview. yeah.

534
00:32:25.820 --> 00:32:28.960
There was a lot of patience in that interview.

535
00:32:48.440 --> 00:32:49.650
- Mm-mm.

536
00:32:56.480 --> 00:32:58.310
Mm...

537
00:33:33.200 --> 00:33:38.030
- I interviewed Wade Wilson for a couple hours.

538
00:33:38.100 --> 00:33:39.410
It could have gone longer.

539
00:33:39.480 --> 00:33:42.060
but he wasn't going to give me any more information.

540
00:33:42.130 --> 00:33:45.100
And then we executed a search warrant for his DNA.

541
00:33:45.170 --> 00:33:46.860
and we took some pictures of him.

542
00:33:46.930 --> 00:33:49.170
looking for injuries and stuff like that.

543
00:33:52.310 --> 00:33:53.820
- At the same time.

544
00:33:53.890 --> 00:33:56.750
I'm still looking for Diane Ruiz.

545
00:33:59.790 --> 00:34:01.580
- I didn't know where she was.

546
00:34:13.650 --> 00:34:16.200
- Tonight. continuing coverage of the disappearance

547
00:34:16.270 --> 00:34:17.620
of Diane Ruiz

548
00:34:17.680 --> 00:34:20.580
and the death investigation of Kristine Melton.

549
00:34:20.650 --> 00:34:25.750
- Friends and family prayed for Diane Ruiz's safe return.

550
00:34:25.820 --> 00:34:27.060
- A lot of man-hours and time

551
00:34:27.130 --> 00:34:28.750
is being put into both of these.

552
00:34:28.820 --> 00:34:30.750
and they're both being taken very seriously.

553
00:34:30.820 --> 00:34:33.310
And we've also used outside resources.

554
00:34:33.370 --> 00:34:36.240
- It is really chilling to see him--

555
00:34:36.310 --> 00:34:39.410
you know. just knowing he was right in front of my house.

556
00:34:39.480 --> 00:34:42.170
- Abbott says his home-security footage

557
00:34:42.240 --> 00:34:44.890
shows the black Nissan police were looking for

558
00:34:44.960 --> 00:34:47.480
speeding down his street.

559
00:34:47.550 --> 00:34:48.750
- Kind of the scary thing--

560
00:34:48.820 --> 00:34:51.410
you don't know if the body was in there.

561
00:34:51.480 --> 00:34:53.310
- We had search parties out.

562
00:34:53.370 --> 00:34:57.200
We were searching any wooded area

563
00:34:57.270 --> 00:34:59.240
in that vicinity

564
00:34:59.310 --> 00:35:01.410
of where her cell phone was pinging.

565
00:35:01.480 --> 00:35:04.510
any vacant homes. anywhere that--

566
00:35:04.580 --> 00:35:06.130
hide a body.

567
00:35:09.340 --> 00:35:11.410
- It was two days after he was arrested.

568
00:35:11.480 --> 00:35:14.720
I got a call from that same detective.

569
00:35:14.790 --> 00:35:17.750
And she asked me. she said.

570
00:35:17.820 --> 00:35:21.100
do you think that Wade would talk to you?

571
00:35:21.170 --> 00:35:24.720
And I said. yeah. I think he'll talk to me.

572
00:35:24.790 --> 00:35:26.240
And I asked her why.

573
00:35:26.310 --> 00:35:30.480
And she said. you know. we're searching for Diane's body.

574
00:35:30.550 --> 00:35:33.060
and we can't find her.

575
00:35:33.130 --> 00:35:36.200
So the next day. I went in to visit him.

576
00:35:39.550 --> 00:35:43.930
- At that time. he was in a suicide suit.

577
00:35:44.000 --> 00:35:46.480
He had threatened to commit suicide while over there.

578
00:35:46.550 --> 00:35:49.370
It's a large green suit.

579
00:35:49.440 --> 00:35:51.620
It goes over your head and shoulders.

580
00:35:51.680 --> 00:35:53.930
We call it a turtle suit. because it does--

581
00:35:54.000 --> 00:35:55.240
it looks like.

582
00:35:55.310 --> 00:35:57.370
you know. someone in a turtle shell. basically.

583
00:36:06.200 --> 00:36:08.720
He looked at me. and he said...

584
00:36:08.790 --> 00:36:10.410
Dad...

585
00:36:10.480 --> 00:36:12.480
did you turn me in?

586
00:36:52.960 --> 00:36:54.510
- When I say that to you...

587
00:37:57.790 --> 00:37:59.200
I said. listen...

588
00:38:01.310 --> 00:38:03.370
You know. the second woman--

589
00:38:03.440 --> 00:38:06.310
I said. you know she has two kids. right?

590
00:38:14.890 --> 00:38:16.550
- I want my mother to come home.

591
00:38:16.620 --> 00:38:17.820
That's my mother.

592
00:39:00.370 --> 00:39:02.130
- He had tears in his eyes.

593
00:39:02.200 --> 00:39:04.240
And he said. well. what do I do?

594
00:39:04.310 --> 00:39:06.650
I said. you tell the truth. son.

595
00:39:06.720 --> 00:39:08.200
I said. you tell the truth.

596
00:39:11.790 --> 00:39:13.000
- Yeah.

597
00:39:33.310 --> 00:39:36.240
He asked me. you know. will you tell the detectives

598
00:39:36.310 --> 00:39:38.130
to come talk to me?

599
00:39:38.200 --> 00:39:40.130
And I'll tell them the truth.

600
00:40:37.130 --> 00:40:38.410
- Diane Ruiz's cell phone

601
00:40:38.480 --> 00:40:40.510
had pinged off of cell towers in this area.

602
00:40:40.580 --> 00:40:43.370
So we concentrated our search for a couple of days

603
00:40:43.440 --> 00:40:44.720
without any luck.

604
00:40:44.790 --> 00:40:46.060
And then we had--

605
00:40:46.130 --> 00:40:48.720
two of our officers were eating lunch

606
00:40:48.790 --> 00:40:50.680
in the vacant field over here.

607
00:40:50.750 --> 00:40:52.620
And while they were eating lunch.

608
00:40:52.680 --> 00:40:55.820
they noticed that there was a buzzard flying around.

609
00:40:55.890 --> 00:40:59.240
And they watched that buzzard. you know. drop down

610
00:40:59.310 --> 00:41:01.580
into the vacant field behind me.

611
00:41:01.650 --> 00:41:03.750
And they went and took a look.

612
00:41:03.820 --> 00:41:06.370
and. sure enough. that's when they found Diane Ruiz

613
00:41:06.440 --> 00:41:08.480
in the bushes.

614
00:41:08.550 --> 00:41:11.960
Her pants had been partially removed from her body.

615
00:41:12.030 --> 00:41:15.000
And she was in stages of decomposition

616
00:41:15.060 --> 00:41:17.680
from being there for a couple of days.

617
00:41:19.960 --> 00:41:22.410
It was probably two hours into the scene now

618
00:41:22.480 --> 00:41:23.890
that I get a phone call

619
00:41:23.960 --> 00:41:26.720
from the Lee County Sheriff's Office

620
00:41:26.790 --> 00:41:29.060
telling me that. hey.

621
00:41:29.130 --> 00:41:32.890
Wade Wilson asked for you to come over here.

622
00:41:32.960 --> 00:41:34.820
He wants to talk to you.

623
00:41:34.890 --> 00:41:37.960
He didn't know at that point that I--

624
00:41:38.030 --> 00:41:40.890
or we had already found Diane Ruiz.

625
00:41:40.960 --> 00:41:42.820
so I just played along.

626
00:41:47.480 --> 00:41:50.270
So the very first thing that he had told me was.

627
00:41:50.340 --> 00:41:52.580
is that he wanted me

628
00:41:52.650 --> 00:41:56.860
to provide him with a hamburger and French fries.

629
00:41:56.930 --> 00:41:59.890
And he would. in turn. show me

630
00:41:59.960 --> 00:42:02.310
where Diane Ruiz was located.

631
00:42:22.790 --> 00:42:25.200
- I knew that that wasn't going to happen.

632
00:42:25.270 --> 00:42:27.480
but I didn't want to tell him that at first.

633
00:42:27.550 --> 00:42:31.200
I wanted to find out more. you know. details. like I said.

634
00:42:31.270 --> 00:42:33.340
about what actually happened.

635
00:43:06.170 --> 00:43:08.650
- He said in his confession he was looking for someone.

636
00:43:08.720 --> 00:43:10.750
And when he saw her. he said. oh. that's her.

637
00:43:10.820 --> 00:43:12.820
I'm gonna get her. I'm gonna kill her.

638
00:44:08.270 --> 00:44:10.620
- Good afternoon. everybody. Thank you so much for coming.

639
00:44:10.680 --> 00:44:12.750
I am State Attorney Amira Fox.

640
00:44:12.820 --> 00:44:14.060
And I stand here today

641
00:44:14.130 --> 00:44:16.750
with Cape Coral Police Chief Dave Newlan.

642
00:44:16.820 --> 00:44:18.620
Detective Bell. and Detective Jones.

643
00:44:18.680 --> 00:44:20.960
and our teams from both our offices

644
00:44:21.030 --> 00:44:25.200
to announce the indictment of Wade Steven Wilson

645
00:44:25.270 --> 00:44:29.240
for the murders of Kristine Melton. age 35.

646
00:44:29.310 --> 00:44:32.550
and Diane Ruiz. 43.

647
00:44:32.620 --> 00:44:34.270
both of Cape Coral.

648
00:44:34.340 --> 00:44:36.580
Once in a while. a case comes along

649
00:44:36.650 --> 00:44:41.240
where you truly have an absolutely evil person.

650
00:44:41.310 --> 00:44:43.650
and this is one of those cases.

651
00:45:56.100 --> 00:45:59.410
- We do this because of victims and their families

652
00:45:59.480 --> 00:46:01.310
in front of a worldwide audience

653
00:46:01.370 --> 00:46:04.480
to make sure that that evil killer

654
00:46:04.550 --> 00:46:07.240
got the penalty that we thought was the appropriate penalty.

655
00:46:10.480 --> 00:46:13.240
- And this is one of those cases.

656
00:46:21.750 --> 00:46:24.100
- We've gained enough worldwide fame.

657
00:46:24.170 --> 00:46:25.750
You're talking about who's the most famous right now.

658
00:46:25.820 --> 00:46:26.750
It's me.

659
00:46:26.820 --> 00:46:28.440
- Wade Wilson... - For Wade Wilson...

660
00:46:28.510 --> 00:46:29.750
- Wade Wilson.

661
00:46:29.820 --> 00:46:32.340
- This case exploded. - This went worldwide.

662
00:46:32.410 --> 00:46:34.100
- To Wade Wilson. - Wade Wilson.

663
00:46:34.170 --> 00:46:36.410
- He had girls all around the world

664
00:46:36.480 --> 00:46:38.170
writing him. sending him money.

665
00:46:38.240 --> 00:46:40.930
- At one point. a GoFundMe account was set up.

666
00:46:41.000 --> 00:46:45.720
- Wilson has received over 3.900 messages.

667
00:46:45.790 --> 00:46:48.270
- I love you so much. baby.

668
00:46:48.340 --> 00:46:50.550
Baby. you know we can still get married. right?

668
